      <hedline>
        <hl1>Whimsy In Sterling</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By ELAINE LOUIE</byline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>SILVER has been transformed into a bowl with sharp, dangerous-looking teeth and a chalice fit for ancient knights on holy quests at "A Sterling Exhibition."</p>
        <p>The show of 120 objects by 38 American silversmiths is at the Pritam &amp; Eames Gallery, 29 Race Lane in East Hampton, L.I., through June 30. "The objects range from colonial to arts and crafts to funky," said Jeffrey Herman, director of the Society of American Silversmiths in Providence, R.I., a co-producer of the show.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>SILVER has been transformed into a bowl with sharp, dangerous-looking teeth and a chalice fit for ancient knights on holy quests at "A Sterling Exhibition."</p>
        <p>The show of 120 objects by 38 American silversmiths is at the Pritam &amp; Eames Gallery, 29 Race Lane in East Hampton, L.I., through June 30. "The objects range from colonial to arts and crafts to funky," said Jeffrey Herman, director of the Society of American Silversmiths in Providence, R.I., a co-producer of the show.</p>
        <p>"Drambuie Decanter" by Sue Amendolara, above ($5,000) has a slate and silver stopper studded with coral, and a curvaceous body seemingly wrapped in gold wings.</p>
        <p>CURRENTS</p>
      </block>
